# Truegrynd – Product Rules

## What Truegrynd Is
A B2C web app for async fitness competition. Users submit scores on standardized challenges and compete on a global leaderboard. Free to play, community-driven (UGC).

## What It Is NOT
- Not a workout tracker (no sets/reps logging for personal training)
- Not a social network (no following, no DMs, no feed of activity)
- Not a video hosting platform (we never store videos — only external URLs)

## MVP Scope (build only this)
1. Auth (Google / Apple / Email via Supabase)
2. Onboarding: biometric profile + simplified initiation (3 easy challenges) + faction choice
3. Challenge feed with leaderboard per challenge
4. Score submission (optional proof; required to rank)
5. Finisher Card generation (canvas image) + native share
6. User profile with history and trophies

## Factions
Three factions: `nomads`, `horde`, `iron_alliance`
- User belongs to one faction (chosen at onboarding, cannot change in MVP)
- Faction score = sum of individual member scores

## Smart Proof Logic
- Users can submit scores **with or without** a video URL
- Video URL must be a YouTube or TikTok link (non-listed accepted)
- **Leaderboard shows only validated scores** (`is_validated: true`)
- A score is **validated** (and ranked) only when a valid video URL is provided
- Scores without video are saved but **not ranked** (`is_validated: false`)

## Leaderboard Filters
- Global (all users)
- By sex (male / female / other)
- By age bracket (18–29, 30–39, 40–49, 50+)
- By faction

## Score Types
- `time`: lower is better (formatted as MM:SS)
- `reps`: higher is better (integer)
